	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=1&mid=101846078114410>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=1&mid=101846078114410>RE: What weapons to hold in which hand ?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=1&mid=101846078114410#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Apr 10th 1:51 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93579><span id=Sage>Yosa</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>175 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.56]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>As a general rule your best damage weapon should be in your main hand.&nbsp;&nbsp;By best damage I mean the one with the lower ratio, or higher damage per sec (dps).  Also if you feel that the proc of a lower dps weapon makes it a better damage weapon over all then use it in your primary.  <br><br>As you get higher lvl it becomes more difficult to determain which weapon has the best damage rate.  This is do the the str bonus on weapons held in your primary hand.  Since the damage bonus is the same for all weapons (one handed weapons) faster weapons with lower dps can actually do more damage.  <br><br>It used to be that a wurmy was the cheepest uber weapon, and usualy the first uber weapon to be obtained by a warrior.  Since it was my first uber weapon I developed some general rules on how to determain if a lower dps, fast weapon would out damage the wurmy.  <br>1. To beat the wurmy the weapon should have damage equil to or higher than about half of the delay. <br>2. To beat the wurmy the weapon must have a delay of 23 or less.  <br>3. Unless your looking at a jade mace class weapon or better it is hard to beat the wurmy before lvl 50.  <br><br>Since the lanch of luclin the lamy and other weapons have come down a lot in cost.<br><br>I would say that after lvl 35 or so the wurmy, lamy and GSC are all about the same.<br><br>There are a number of other weapons that work well as primary hand weapons that can be switch to off hand if you get a better (faster) <br>The JSM is a good example, as are them many differnt weapons with 12/26.  Same with the Centi swords.  Post lvl 53 you really shold have a weapon that meets rule one and two above.  <br><br>Currently I use a OSG (10/18) as my primary weapon and a RBSoN (12/26 176dd) as my off hand weapon.  </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
